        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Large Fish Feed Mill with Production Capacity of 20 Ton/Per Day&quot; scheme was launched by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India under the Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY), it aims to strengthen post-harvest infrastructure and enhance fish feed production to support sustainable aquaculture. Under this scheme, a grant is provided to beneficiaries for setting up a large fish feed mill, with 40% subsidy for general category and 60% for Scheduled Caste/Women beneficiaries. \n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Monetary Assistance:**\n\n- Grant of ₹20,00,000/- per unit for establishing a fish feed mill with 20-ton/day capacity.\n\n**Subsidy Provisions:**\n\n- 40% subsidy on unit cost for General Category beneficiaries.\n- 60% subsidy on unit cost for Scheduled Caste and women beneficiaries.\n\n<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to strengthen aquaculture through fish feed production. It provides a grant per unit to the beneficiaries under PMMSY.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
